						<summary>

						<p>This records the provision made by two ladies for burning a ‘half’ and a ‘quarter’ perpetual lamp in the temple by bringing into cultivation two pieces of land in <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> village Erukkāṭṭuchchēri for that purpose. Tirukkaḍavūr is stated to be in Ākkūr-nāḍu a division of Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
